  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "name": "grype",
          "version": "0.115.0",
          "informationUri": "https://github.com/anchore/grype",
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "CVE-2024-7264-curl",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2024-7264 low vulnerability for curl package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in libcurl, where libcurl's ASN1 parser code has the `GTime2str()` function, used for parsing an ASN.1 Generalized Time field. If a syntactically incorrect field is given, the parser can use -1 for the length of the *time fraction*, leading to a `strlen()` performed on a pointer to a heap buffer area that is not purposely NULL terminated."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-7264",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2024-7264\nSeverity: low\nPackage: curl\nVersion: 8.12.1-4.el10\nFix Version: \nType: rpm\nLocation: /usr/lib/sysimage/rpm/rpmdb.sqlite\nData Namespace: redhat:distro:redhat:10\nLink: [CVE-2024-7264](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-7264)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2024-7264**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| low  | curl  | 8.12.1-4.el10  |   | rpm  | /usr/lib/sysimage/rpm/rpmdb.sqlite  | redhat:distro:redhat:10  | [CVE-2024-7264](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-7264)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:rpm/rocky/curl@8.12.1-4.el10?arch=x86_64\u0026distro=rocky-10.2\u0026upstream=curl-8.12.1-4.el10.src.rpm"
                ],
                "security-severity": "5.3"
              }
            },
