            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-42768-openssl-fips-provider",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-42768 low vulnerability for openssl-fips-provider package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in OpenSSL's CMS_decrypt() and PKCS7_decrypt() functions. This vulnerability, a Bleichenbacher-style oracle, could allow a remote attacker to decrypt or sign messages using the victim's private RSA key. Exploitation requires the attacker to provide specially crafted CMS or S/MIME messages and observe the application's error codes or decryption output. While the attack is technically possible, the specific conditions required make it unlikely to be exploited in typical deployments."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-42768",
