              "id": "CVE-2026-42770-openssl-fips-provider",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-42770 low vulnerability for openssl-fips-provider package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in OpenSSL. A malicious peer can exploit this vulnerability by presenting a specially crafted DHX (X9.42) peer key. Due to improper validation of the peer key's subgroup membership, an attacker can recover the victim's private key after a small number of key exchange attempts. This information disclosure can lead to unauthorized access or further compromise of affected systems."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-42770",
